---
title: One Pot Spicy Rigatoni alla Rossa with Fresh Rigatoni, Mozzarella & Spinach
description: For our chefs' version of rigatoni rosa ("pink" in Italian), you’ll make a quick homemade tomato sauce swirled with cream cheese and seasoned with chili flakes (for a little heat!). Toss in tender fresh rigatoni pasta that cooks in a flash, then stir in spinach, top with fresh mozzarella, and get ready to blush from all the compliments.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/67325af6ba08659748634749-9f208505.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/67325af6ba08659748634749-en-US.pdf
time required: 15 minutes
cuisine: Southern Europe
nutrition:
  calories: 610 kcal
  fat: 26 g
  saturated fat: 13 g
  carbohydrates: 68 g
  sugar: 16 g
  protein: 23 g
  fiber: 4 g
  sodium: 980 mg
servings: 2
course: main course
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/one-pot-spicy-rigatoni-alla-rossa-67325af6ba08659748634749
author: Sara Heilman
---

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{} in a large #pot over medium heat. Add @tomato paste{1%unit}, @Italian seasoning{1%tablespoon}, @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, @veggie stock concentrate{1%unit}, and @chili flakes{1%teaspoon} to taste (we used 1⁄8 tsp; 1⁄4 tsp for 4 servings). Cook, stirring, until fragrant and tomato paste darkens in color, ~{30-60%seconds}.

Whisk @cream cheese{4%tablespoon} into #pot with sauce mixture. Cook, whisking, until melted and combined, ~{20-30%seconds}.

Wash and dry produce.

Stir @fresh rigatoni pasta{7%ounce} and @water{2%cups} (3 cups for 4 servings) into #pot with sauce mixture; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. (TIP: Gently separate rigatoni with your hands before adding to pot.) Increase heat to medium high and bring to a simmer.

Cook, stirring constantly, until rigatoni is tender and sauce is creamy and thickened, ~{5-6%minutes}. (TIP: Gently scrape rigatoni from bottom of pot if it begins to stick.) Remove from heat.

Add @spinach{5%ounce} and stir until wilted, ~{30-60%seconds}.

> Depending on the size of your pot, you may need to add spinach in batches––stir in a splash of water to help spinach wilt if needed.

Tear @fresh mozzarella{4%ounce} into bite-size pieces and sprinkle evenly over pasta. Season with salt and pepper.

Divide pasta between shallow bowls or serve family style with any remaining chili flakes on the side.